# 4) merge back onto snap_speed and rename
snap_speed = (
    snap_speed
      .merge(top, on='nflId', how='inner')
      .rename(columns={'s':'snap_s',
                       'a':'snap_a',
                       'los_diff':'snap_los_diff'})
)
Reason: In the original implementation we only aggregated posTeam == 1 (offense) and posTeam == 0 (defense). The optimized version was inadvertently including any other posTeam values present in the data, which led to an extra nflId group in the final merge and thus a shape mismatch. By filtering df to posTeam.isin([0,1]) before the combined aggregation, we exactly match the set of (gameId, playId, nflId) groups the original code considered. This restores the identical nflId list and fixes the one-row discrepancy in the merge.
